Package lab4.cscd210lab4methods

Class CSCD210Lab4Methods

  • java.lang.Object
    • lab4.cscd210lab4methods.CSCD210Lab4Methods
  • public class CSCD210Lab4Methods
extends Object
    This is the methods for Lab4. This is very similar to Lab2 but instead we are learning methods and how to write code based on a provided API.
    NOTE: When you pass parameters to methods you will put final before the type
    For Example: the method header for readName would be public static String readName(final Scanner kb)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        String Representing a valid first space middle space last
        Throws:

      • determineMiddleName

        public static String determineMiddleName​(String name)
        The determineMiddleName extracts the middle name from the string passed in. You are guaranteed the string will contain first space middle space last. You must use the split method to extract the middle name.

        Returns:
        String Representing the middle name that has been trimmed of white space
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if name is null or name is blank

      • determineHashCode

        public static int determineHashCode​(int birthYear,
                                    String middle)
        The determineHashCode simple determines the hash code value by adding the primitive year constant to the primitive birth year that is passed in to the primitive that is returned by calling the hashCode method on the middle name that is passed in
        Parameters:
        birthYear - Representing the birth year as an int
        middle - Representing the middle name as a String
        Returns:
        int Representing the primitive constant YEAR plus the primitive int birthYear plus the primitive int by calling the hashCode on middle
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if middle is null or middle is blank
        IllegalArgumentException - if birthYear is less than or equal to 1900
